      "id": "SKY-003",
      "title": "Implement flight search CLI entry point with formatted table output",
      "agentRole": "typescript-engineer",
      "agentGroup": "independent",
      "status": "completed",
      "completed": true,
      "description": "Create `src/cli.ts` — a standalone Node entry point that accepts flight search arguments via `process.argv` and prints results as an aligned table. Parse flags manually (no commander, no yargs, zero new runtime deps). Require `RAPIDAPI_KEY` env var; exit 1 with a human-readable message if absent. Instantiate `SkyscannerClient` from `src/skyscanner-client.ts` (SKY-002), call `searchFlights` forwarding all parsed arguments including adults count, and render results in a dynamically-padded table with columns: Airline | Price | Departure | Arrival | Duration | Stops. Column widths are determined by the widest value in each column (including the header). A separator row of hyphen characters must appear between the header and data rows. Price is right-aligned and prefixed with the currency symbol returned by the API (default £ if absent); all other columns are left-aligned. If no flights are returned print `No flights found.` and exit 0. On any thrown error print the message to stderr and exit 1. Create `src/cli.test.ts` covering argument validation, successful render, empty-result render, missing env var, and error handling using vitest with `SkyscannerClient` mocked at the module boundary. The compiled output must be invokable as `node dist/cli.js ...` after `tsc`; `tsconfig.json` must have `outDir` set to `dist` and emit CommonJS-compatible output.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": [
        "`src/cli.ts` exists and `tsc --noEmit` reports zero errors",
        "`tsconfig.json` sets `outDir` to `dist` and emits a module format compatible with `node dist/cli.js` invocation (CommonJS or ESM with .mjs extension consistently applied)",
        "Flags `--from`, `--to`, and `--date` are all required; if any is absent the CLI prints a usage hint to stderr (showing correct flag names) and exits with code 2",
        "The `--date` flag value must match the pattern `YYYY-MM-DD`; a value that does not match this format causes exit code 2 with a human-readable message written to stderr before any network call is made",
        "Optional `--adults` flag defaults to 1 when omitted; a non-integer value, a value ≤ 0, or a non-numeric string causes exit code 2 with a human-readable message to stderr",
        "The parsed `adults` value is forwarded as an argument to `SkyscannerClient.searchFlights` — the flag is not silently dropped",
        "If `RAPIDAPI_KEY` env var is unset or empty, CLI prints 'Error: RAPIDAPI_KEY environment variable is required' to stderr and exits 1 before making any network call",
        "When `searchFlights` resolves with one or more results, stdout contains: (a) a header row with columns Airline, Price, Departure, Arrival, Duration, Stops; (b) a separator row of hyphen characters whose width matches each column exactly; (c) one data row per result; all columns padded to the width of the widest value in that column (including the header label)",
        "All columns except Price are left-aligned within their padded width; the Price column is right-aligned within its padded width",
        "Price column values are prefixed with the currency symbol from the API response; if the API response omits a currency symbol, £ is used as the fallback",
