          "reviewNotes": "speckit added genuine correctness value: the listen() guard AC (app export alone is insufficient — a bare import during vitest will still bind a port without the guard), FlightResult type-import AC (enforces SKY-002 dependency and prevents silent type drift between layers), non-numeric adults → 400 AC (closes a validation gap), searchedAt distinctness tightened to '1 ms apart', and 503 scope correctly narrowed to API routes only with /health and / explicitly unaffected. The build script AC is a practical addition. Final 23 ACs are well-formed and non-overlapping. However, the BLOCKING gap called out explicitly in the coordinator notes was NOT resolved by speckit: the server URL query params use `from`/`to` while SkyscannerClient.SearchParams uses `origin`/`destination` — no AC requires this mapping translation to be implemented or tested. An implementor following the ACs as written can pass all 8 mandated tests while forwarding `from` directly into a `from` key on SearchParams, which the client will silently ignore or reject at runtime. Every /search and /cheapest request will fail in production. This translation must be added as an explicit AC with a corresponding test before the story is buildable. The CORS/security-headers deferral was noted but no explicit scope decision was recorded.",
